586
00:53:14,610 --> 00:53:17,410
I, Kang Han Su, offered to defend her.

587
00:53:17,410 --> 00:53:21,740
I told her I'd get her acquittedâ€”not exile or slave-labor punishment!

588
00:53:21,740 --> 00:53:24,020
Are you getting angry at the new bride?

589
00:53:24,020 --> 00:53:26,500
I am baffled.

590
00:53:26,500 --> 00:53:29,310
Well, it is better than taking the case and things going awry.

591
00:53:29,310 --> 00:53:31,870
I am saying I could save her because I could.

592
00:53:31,870 --> 00:53:33,690
But how?

593
00:53:33,690 --> 00:53:36,410
The law was not meant to kill a person.

594
00:53:36,410 --> 00:53:39,290
It was meant to save a person.

595
00:53:41,060 --> 00:53:43,270
I wanted to give her a chance.

596
00:53:43,270 --> 00:53:50,580
The innocent will get to live, and the guilty will end up paying for their crime.

597
00:53:51,730 --> 00:53:55,180
Once she realizes such an obvious truth,

598
00:53:55,180 --> 00:53:58,550
even if she faces difficulties like this again,

599
00:53:58,550 --> 00:54:01,940
she will not make such a foolish choice as she did today.

600
00:54:01,940 --> 00:54:05,470
By doing so, I wanted to cheer on the new bride,

601
00:54:05,470 --> 00:54:10,030
who chose to kill rather than kill herself.

602
00:54:12,060 --> 00:54:13,750
Geez! But what is the use?

603
00:54:13,750 --> 00:54:16,380
She threw away her own good fortune.

604
00:54:16,380 --> 00:54:18,210
What if she comes back?

605
00:54:18,210 --> 00:54:20,950
Will you save her as you promised her?

606
00:54:20,950 --> 00:54:24,750
How about you? Are you still against it?

607
00:54:24,750 --> 00:54:29,490
I do not believe that the crime of killing a person should be forgiven for any reason.

608
00:54:29,490 --> 00:54:33,320
So do you want that new bride to be punished?

609
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:39,270
I do want to hear how you plan to defend her state of mind.

610
00:54:41,120 --> 00:54:44,690
Yes. I want to be persuaded by you, sir.

611
00:54:45,460 --> 00:54:49,940
If you persuade me, you could probably persuade the king as well.

612
00:54:49,940 --> 00:54:52,090
